      <title>Build and release systems for QOwnNotes for Linux, Mac OS X and Windows!</title>
      <link>http://www.qownnotes.org/Blog/Build-and-release-systems-for-QOwnNotes-for-Linux-Mac-OS-X-and-Windows</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Finally all build and release systems for &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.qownnotes.org" target="_blank"&gt;QOwnNotes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; for Linux, Mac OS X and Windows are running well and you always can download the latest release!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I'm using &lt;b&gt;Travis CI&lt;/b&gt; for &lt;b&gt;Ubuntu Linux&lt;/b&gt;, visit &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://travis-ci.org/pbek/QOwnNotes" target="_blank"&gt;QOwnNotes on Travis CI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;GitLab CI&lt;/b&gt; is used for creating the &lt;b&gt;Mac OS X&lt;/b&gt; builds, visit &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://ci.gitlab.com/projects/5070?ref=develop" target="_blank"&gt;QOwnNotes on GitLab CI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And &lt;b&gt;AppVeyor&lt;/b&gt; is used for creating the builds for &lt;b&gt;Microsoft Windows&lt;/b&gt;, visit &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://ci.appveyor.com/project/pbek/qownnotes" target="_blank"&gt;QOwnNotes on AppVeyor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You will find all the &lt;b&gt;new binaries&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.qownnotes.org/#downloads" target="_blank"&gt;download area of the project page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
