    <item>
      <title>Links to other notes or files are now possible in QOwnNotes</title>
      <link>http://www.qownnotes.org/Blog/Links-to-other-notes-or-files-are-now-possible-in-QOwnNotes</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Build 25 of &lt;b&gt;QOwnNotes&lt;/b&gt; brings better url handling in the &lt;b&gt;markdown preview mode&lt;/b&gt;. &lt;b&gt;Links&lt;/b&gt; to &lt;b&gt;other notes&lt;/b&gt; or &lt;b&gt;files&lt;/b&gt; are now possible!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
Examples:&lt;br /&gt;
- &amp;lt;note://MyNote&amp;gt; opens the note &amp;quot;MyNote&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
- &amp;lt;note://my-note-with-spaces-in-the-name&amp;gt; opens the note &amp;quot;My Note with spaces in the name&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
- &amp;lt;http://www.bekerle.com/QOwnNotes&amp;gt; opens the webpage&lt;br /&gt;- &amp;lt;file:///path/to/my/file/QOwnNotes.pdf&amp;gt; opens the file &amp;quot;/path/to/my/file/QOwnNotes.pdf&amp;quot; if the operating system supports that handler&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You will find the &lt;b&gt;new binaries&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.bekerle.com/QOwnNotes#downloads" target="_self"&gt;download area of the project page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=""&gt;&lt;div class="content-view-embed"&gt;
    &lt;div class="class-image"&gt;
        &lt;div class="attribute-image"&gt;
            

    
        
    
